- Continue component design and procurement components to build Prototype Weapon Assemblies in preparation of future
ground tests.
- Continue ground tests of Prototype Weapon Assemblies to include mechanical, electrical, subscale, and sled testing.
- Continue aircraft integration required for flight testing.
- Initiate flight testing activities.
- Complete subscale component and subsystem testing.
- Complete sled test target construction.
FY 2025 to FY 2026 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2026 increased compared to FY 2025 by $17.847 million due to greater emphasis on prototype design after completion
of Modeling and Simulation of mission effectiveness of design space options; increased procurement and development of
components; the initiation of subsystem and test unit assembly; and the initiation of ground tests of the Prototype Weapon
Assemblies.
