 aircraft. Considerations in the development of the prototype include nuclear surety, maintenance and logistics, refinement of requirements (Military Characteristics), and
 producibility.

 After successful flight test demonstration of the prototype, the program will mature developmental hardware to nuclear system "diamond stamp” quality, ensure nuclear
 surety standards are met, and mature aircraft interfaces including Aircraft Monitor and Control functions.

