FY 2025 Plans:
- Mature open interface standards to include: mission planning data modeling, subsystem enhancements
- Develop Long-Range Kill Chain (LRKC) configuration specifications for data links
- Conduct initial integration activities for alignment with Common Flexible Weapon (CFW) Interface
- Upgrade and maintain software certification tool to support planned implementation platforms
- Update user interface tool to ease implementation and reduce specialized training
FY 2026 Plans:
- Continue technical maturation of the UAI standard
- Implement and continue development of LRKC configuration specifications for data links
- Integrate the UAI and CFW interfaces into a common open armament interface
- Continue to maintain currency of the source of truth for DAF-owned open armament standards
- Increase model-based system engineering (MBSE) products within open standards for rapid digital integration by adopting
platforms
FY 2025 to FY 2026 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY26 funding increases due to inflation and growth of open armament interface development required to support Long Range
Kill Chain configuration and implementation. In addition, it includes scope to integrate the UAI and Common Flexible Weapon
interfaces into a common armament interface.
