Remarks
 FINANCIAL PERFORMANCE: HH-60W is evaluated against traditional Research and Development (R&D) program expenditure benchmarks. Unlike many traditional R&D
 programs, however, the HH-60W EMD contract is a Fixed Price Incentive Fee (FPIF) contract with progress payments. Ten (10%) percent of incurred costs are withheld
 until the end of the contract, when they are liquidated. Mandatory funding obligations and progress payment withholds will cause the program to lag traditional expenditure
 benchmarks, painting an inaccurate portrait of overall program health.

FY 2020+: Transitioned Management Services to APAF.




